{"id": 286, "title": "Ticket #286: ImageSize and DiskUsage decrease", "description": "<blockquote>\nBoth <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=DiskUsage\" title=\"Disk Usage\">DiskUsage</a></span> and <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ImageSize\" title=\"Image Size\">ImageSize</a></span> are allowed to decrease when receiving updates for a job.  The concensus is that this is not intentional.  I noticed it because at HEP, we submit most jobs with a large <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=DiskUsage\" title=\"Disk Usage\">DiskUsage</a></span> value, but after the job has tried to run once, this value is getting set to something much smaller.\n\n<p>The problem appears to go back to a commit back in Nov of 2005 by Nate Mueller, c55bbe4c94ec67792e28ae1fdaa8b790932e4883</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2009-Feb-27 13:32</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8400ff6e2728aa21970d56ac8e29c079adf95bc0\">[14087]</a></span>: <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ImageSize\" title=\"Image Size\">ImageSize</a></span> and <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=DiskUsage\" title=\"Disk Usage\">DiskUsage</a></span> were unintentionally allowed to decrease. (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=286\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('286'); return false;\" title=\"ImageSize and DiskUsage decrease\">#286</a></span>)  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2010-Jan-31 13:40", "s